{"schema_version": 2, "source_hash": "13ca416d6d326696", "candidate": {"id": "cand-026", "name": "Arjun Patel", "raw_cv": "ARJUN PATEL\narjun.patel@email.com | London, UK\n\nSENIOR DEVOPS ENGINEER\n\nPROFESSIONAL SUMMARY\nSenior DevOps engineer with 8 years of experience designing and operating cloud-native infrastructure on AWS. Expert in Kubernetes, Terraform, and CI/CD at scale. Strong background in fintech and high-availability production environments.\n\nEXPERIENCE\n\nSenior DevOps Engineer \u2014 Starling Bank, London (2020\u2013present)\n- Own the AWS EKS platform serving 100+ microservices across 3 environments\n- Led migration from EC2 auto-scaling groups to EKS, reducing infrastructure cost 35%\n- Designed and implemented GitOps deployment pipeline (ArgoCD + Helm) adopted across all squads\n- Introduced platform SLOs and built an internal developer portal (Backstage) reducing onboarding time\n- On-call lead for platform incidents; P1 MTTR under 8 minutes\n\nDevOps Engineer \u2014 Funding Circle, London (2018\u20132020)\n- Managed Terraform infrastructure for multi-region AWS setup\n- Built CI/CD pipelines (Jenkins \u2192 GitHub Actions migration) for 40+ services\n- Introduced centralised log aggregation (ELK stack) across the platform\n\nInfrastructure Engineer \u2014 Infosys, London (2016\u20132018)\n- Managed on-premises VMware infrastructure for enterprise clients\n- Certified AWS Solutions Architect \u2013 Associate (2017)\n\nSKILLS\nAWS (EKS, EC2, RDS, S3, IAM, VPC, CloudWatch), Kubernetes, Helm, ArgoCD, Terraform, Ansible, GitHub Actions, Jenkins, Docker, Python, Bash, Prometheus, Grafana, Datadog, ELK\n\nEDUCATION\nBEng Computer Systems \u2014 University of Leicester (2013\u20132016)\n\nCERTIFICATIONS\nAWS Solutions Architect Professional, CKA (Certified Kubernetes Administrator)\n\nRIGHT TO WORK\nBritish citizen (Indian heritage)", "raw_linkedin": "Senior DevOps engineer at Starling Bank, running the Kubernetes platform that everything else runs on. I've spent eight years making cloud infrastructure boring in the best possible way \u2014 automated, observable, and as invisible to developers as possible. I'm particularly interested in internal developer platforms and the intersection of platform engineering and developer experience. CKA and AWS SA Pro certified. London-based, open to senior DevOps, platform engineering, or SRE roles at product companies. Prefer hybrid.", "raw_interview_transcript": "Interviewer: Arjun, thanks for coming in. Tell me about the EKS migration at Starling.\n\nArjun: When I joined, Starling was running on EC2 auto-scaling groups with a fairly manual deployment process \u2014 AMI baking, launch templates, the whole thing. It was expensive and it didn't scale well for the number of services we were building. I made the case for EKS and led the 18-month migration. We moved 100+ services without a single customer-facing incident, which I'm proud of. The key was being very methodical: we ran both environments in parallel, migrated service by service, and had clear rollback criteria for each.\n\nInterviewer: Tell me about the GitOps pipeline.\n\nArjun: After EKS we needed a deployment model that teams could self-serve. I evaluated Flux and ArgoCD and chose ArgoCD for its UI and the fact it's easier to explain to developers who aren't Kubernetes experts. We now have all service configurations in Git, ArgoCD handles reconciliation, and developers can deploy to staging without involving the platform team at all. Production deployments still require a PR approval from platform, but the process is fully automated.\n\nInterviewer: What does your ideal next role look like?\n\nArjun: I want to move into a proper platform engineering function \u2014 somewhere thinking seriously about developer experience as a product, not just infrastructure as a cost centre. I'd also like to take on more people management: I've been informally mentoring two engineers at Starling and I'd like that to be formalised.\n\nInterviewer: Salary?\n\nArjun: I'm at \u00a396,000. I'd be looking for \u00a3105\u2013115,000.", "years_experience": 8.0, "skills": ["AWS", "EKS", "EC2", "RDS", "S3", "IAM", "VPC", "CloudWatch", "Kubernetes", "Helm", "ArgoCD", "Terraform", "Ansible", "GitHub Actions", "Jenkins", "Docker", "Python", "Bash", "Prometheus", "Grafana", "Datadog", "ELK", "GitOps", "CI/CD", "Platform Engineering", "SRE", "Internal Developer Platforms"], "industries": ["fintech", "financial services", "banking"], "seniority_level": "senior", "management_experience": false, "education_level": "bachelor", "career_trajectory": "ascending", "interview_score": 0.85, "culture_fit_score": 0.82, "constraints": [{"id": "9776fefa", "type": "hard", "side": "candidate", "category": "compensation", "description": "Current salary \u00a396,000 (baseline from interview)", "canonical_key": "salary_min", "value": 96000.0, "operator": "min", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.98, "currency": "GBP"}, {"id": "d5d7b36c", "type": "hard", "side": "candidate", "category": "compensation", "description": "Looking for \u00a3105\u2013115,000 range (interview statement)", "canonical_key": "salary_min", "value": 105000.0, "operator": "min", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.96, "currency": "GBP"}, {"id": "af1492bd", "type": "hard", "side": "candidate", "category": "compensation", "description": "Upper bound of salary expectation \u00a3105\u2013115,000 (interview)", "canonical_key": "salary_max", "value": 115000.0, "operator": "max", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.96, "currency": "GBP"}, {"id": "7e2f6164", "type": "soft", "side": "candidate", "category": "location", "description": "Prefers hybrid working arrangement (LinkedIn)", "canonical_key": "office_days_per_week", "value": 2.0, "operator": "prefers", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.85, "currency": null}, {"id": "12cd1c3f", "type": "soft", "side": "candidate", "category": "role_type", "description": "Open to senior DevOps, platform engineering, or SRE roles at product companies (LinkedIn)", "canonical_key": null, "value": "platform engineering or SRE", "operator": "prefers", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.92, "currency": null}, {"id": "c88ad110", "type": "soft", "side": "candidate", "category": "role_type", "description": "Wants to move into platform engineering with serious focus on developer experience as a product (interview)", "canonical_key": null, "value": "developer experience focus", "operator": "prefers", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.88, "currency": null}, {"id": "6e340cba", "type": "soft", "side": "candidate", "category": "management", "description": "Would like to take on formalised people management; currently mentoring informally (interview)", "canonical_key": null, "value": "people management responsibilities", "operator": "prefers", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.9, "currency": null}, {"id": "bbba0d7c", "type": "soft", "side": "candidate", "category": "company_type", "description": "Prefers roles at product companies rather than services/consulting (LinkedIn)", "canonical_key": null, "value": "product companies", "operator": "prefers", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.88, "currency": null}], "discipline": "devops"}, "embedding": [-0.00557708740234375, -0.004756927490234375, 0.061004638671875, -0.015777587890625, 0.001972198486328125, 0.030303955078125, 0.007076263427734375, 0.043365478515625, -0.025665283203125, -0.00632476806640625, -0.00852203369140625, -0.041778564453125, -0.007564544677734375, -0.01229095458984375, 0.047393798828125, 0.0288238525390625, -0.02069091796875, -0.0248870849609375, -0.0738525390625, 0.01512908935546875, -0.00534820556640625, -0.01192474365234375, -0.03448486328125, 0.01132965087890625, 0.051605224609375, -0.0006337165832519531, -0.059967041015625, -0.0119476318359375, 0.00336456298828125, -0.03863525390625, 0.04296875, -0.0467529296875, -0.0053558349609375, 0.04791259765625, 0.045806884765625, -0.006916046142578125, 0.00205230712890625, 0.0006589889526367188, 0.01084136962890625, 0.02